nts, armor class, lack of melee ability, and a limited mana pool. While npc casters have a somewhat limited manapool, most don't seem to have any of the other disadvantages that pcs pay to be casters, thus making them essentially warriors who cast. I would ask that you consider scaling down the hitpoints or melee ability of casting mobs, as an npc who can cast for 1200dmg and hits for 250 just like the non-casting warrior npcs in the same dungeon, is over-powered.<br><br>Thanks<br><br><br>Actually, that’s a ‘sort-of-a-bug’ thing… Because NPCs were so stupid about casting spells before, some of them were given improved spell casting abilities to make them relatively better casters. Some of those casters might be too good now, and the team will be looking at those on a case-by-case basis.<br><br>Keep in mind, though, that NPCs can be weak or strong for their ‘level’, and special NPCs can certainly be tougher or weaker than their /con might indicate. Having some of them cast higher level spells is just another tool, just like giving them procs or breath weapons or other innate abilities.<br><br>We’re not forgetting any of those things: we know NPCs have relatively more hit points than PCs, we know they do more damage… we know that stuff.<br><br>You have to keep in mind that these NPCs, though smarter, still don’t have the advantages of being played by human beings. The players get to pick the odds for the most part, they get to pick the timing of the fight and they get to choose from a wide arsenal of classes, spells, items, abilities etc. And a human can put all that stuff together in ways that even our AI code can’t (though I’d love to see NPCs splitting PC spawns.  ).<br><br>That’s the price that NPCs pay, and it’s a pretty big one.<br><br>But we’re keeping our eyes on it, playing against these nifty NPCs ourselves and all that. We’ll make further changes as needed.<br><br>Alan<br><br>------------------------------------------------------------<br><br>I thought this was a well written from Ghanimaa but Alans responce was very disturbing. Sounds like VI threw it in much harder than needed then plans to twink it down. There is a lot of talk on different boards about this.<br><br>I know some players seem this as a challange but casual players suffer dramtically, this backs up VI desire that this is a group only game.<br><br>Just curiuos what fellow druids think?<br><br> <p>Yrehcra<br>Human Druid Preserver<br>55th Season<br>Officer-Mystic Lords, Nameless<br><i>"How can I be out of drink when I have all these ales!"<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umissfoxfyre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Miss Foxfyre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Administrator</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/7/02 6:58:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27552.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://gwynhyfar.homestead.com/files/hm9.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: VI new responce to NPC high end casters</span><hr size=1> Anyone remember this gem of a screenshot from ages ago?<br><br><img src=http://www.darkblood.com/photos/otherside.jpg><br><br><br>Ghanimaa's letter was right on the money, but it is pretty typical of VI to overtune when making changes. In recent history, the first time The Grey was nerfed, the changes were too strong, and they went back and toned it down. The Siren's Grotto entrance was something of an issue once, and that was changed; inside, the zone was too "difficult" and changes were made. Velketor's Labyrinth was once a rather deserted zone due to the overpowered "greens." <br><br>I don't know if this mob tuning will make druids more desirable in dungeon-crawling groups, but it would seem possible for xping. Like I said elsewhere, xping was about the most boring, safe, predictable, and mind-numbing experience next to farming greens for tradeskills -- a lot of people could go afk during xp groups and not worry about it -- but yes, it is not fair that -60 wizard mobs cast Sunstrike, Garrison's, or Elnerick's on you. It's also pretty overpowering for caster mobs to melee like champs (it's nothing new). All in all, some change was needed to make fights harder, but some of the changes were overtuned. :) <p><center><img src="http://www.cityviewsoftware.com/jennifer/forest2.jpg"><br><font size=1>G&nbsp;w&nbsp;y&nbsp;n&nbsp;h&nbsp;y&nbsp;f&nbsp;a&nbsp;r&nbsp;&nbsp;F&nbsp;o&nbsp;x&nbsp;f&nbsp;y&nbsp;r&nbsp;e&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;hierophant&nbsp;&nbsp;in&nbsp;&nbsp;absentia&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;S&nbsp;o&nbsp;l&nbsp;u&nbsp;s&nbsp;e&nbsp;k&nbsp;&nbsp;R&nbsp;o</font></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/useriena.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Seriena</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/7/02 7:51:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27552.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: VI new responce to NPC high end casters</span><hr size=1> Didn't you know that caster balancing meant NPC caster balancing? Come on now. ;p<br><br>Seriously though, you have to admit the NPC casters were rather weak. What's the point of Chardok_Sarnak_01 casting Invoke Fear on a lvl 55+ player? Some of the changes are a bit overboard and need to be toned down but over all I don't think players can complain to much.<br><br>What I think it means for druids though is an even harder time finding groups since people still aren't going to say "We're going to OS, better bring a druid for CoS!". Druids aren't going to be able to keep up with the dmg the new NPC casters are doing. Not even close. Even duoing with a friend is going to be tough, let alone trying to heal an exp group. The Holy Trinity just got stronger imo. I just hope that we're in for a nice big healing upgrade, or buff upgrade even, during priest balancing. <p><br><br><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=117440" TARGET="_NEW">Seriena,</A> 60 druid<br><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=185839" TARGET="_NEW">Joolz,</A> 57 Monk<br><A HREF=http://www.soldiers-of-light.net/>Soldiers of Light</A></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/useriena.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Seriena</A> at: 6/7/02 4:53:33 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugrolmn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grolmn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/7/02 9:20:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27552.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: VI new responce to NPC high end casters</span><hr size=1> Let's not forget how much harder an NPC caster is to interupt as compared to a PC.  4 people beating on a wizard and he still gets the IC off! <p>Peppin Bramblefist<BR>Heirophant of Tarew Marr<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utxbow01.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Txbow 01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/7/02 9:48:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27552.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: VI new responce to NPC high end casters</span><hr s