t.  What were we talking about? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/upacalsidhe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Pacal Sidhe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/7/02 10:17:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27552.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Paladins and wizards &gt; Druids</span><hr size=1> I agree totally here. After bashing away hard against casters last night with my shammy and a group we took the opportunity when the warrior logged to get a pally. It made a huge difference. I even dusted off my SLAM hothey.<br><br>I say keep the caster changes as is but add a new line of spells: casting slows. Give the best version to chanters and the weaker version to shammy. The other option is to add a new line of low damage DoTs to the game that have a chance to disrupt casters every tic for the duration of the DoT. <br><br>In fact you could add a whole range of detrimental spells that are the opposites of the benificial focus items.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubatou062671.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Batou062671</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/7/02 10:28:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27552.topic&index=9>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Paladins and wizards &gt; Druids</span><hr size=1> Bah, give the casting slows to some classes that need somthing important to do...  Like druids, and SK's, maby wizards or some other less desirable class.  <p>Batou of The Nexus<BR>Heirophant of Farsight<BR>Karana Server</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umissfoxfyre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Miss Foxfyre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Administrator</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/7/02 10:33:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27552.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://gwynhyfar.homestead.com/files/hm9.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Paladins and wizards &gt; Druids</span><hr size=1> What. I want a spell that makes caster NPCs fizzle. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufiremynd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Firemynd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/7/02 11:25:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27552.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Paladins and wizards &gt; Druids</span><hr size=1> /shout Druid starting group. Need 5 pallies.<br><br>Alan is rationalizing a BAD THING and not doing a very good job of it. Not at all.<br><br>Granted, NPC casters didn't always choose their attack spells sensibly. Their &quot;AI&quot; was a combination of randomization and pre-selection (small lineup of spells assigned to them by designers, to make sure they didn't randomly spawn with nothing but utility spells from their 'class' e.g. enduring breath, which NPCs don't need anyway).<br><br>Each NPC spawned with any/all of the following: a pre-selected set of buffs already active; pre-selected set of spells with which to buff themselves and other nearby NPCs; and pre-selected set of attack and debuff spells to use against player characters. <br><br>But NPC casters were <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  already</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> &quot;balanced&quot; by virtue of the fact that they:<br>- have as many hit points as NPC melee classed counteparts, <br>- melee as well as NPC melee classed counterparts,<br>- have resistances that were as good or better than NPC melee classed counterparts,<br>And they:<br>- have channeling skill suspiciously far above PC casters can ever achieve,<br>- have the odd ability to instantly regenerate hundreds or even thousands of hit points after a successful gate_spell to their spawn point.<br>- have innate RunSpeed3 long before level 51.<br><br>I dare say that if player casters had the first two advantages NPC casters have in the list above, they'd never again mention caster balancing with the degree of desperation you've seen since Velious. But we haven't asked for the same combat and health as melee classes, because we realize those are the disadvantages to having magical abilities. Unfortunately that principle has been so utterly abandoned for NPC casters, that player casters are at an unfair disadvantage.<br><br>Alan:<br><br>You state that player casters have the &quot;advantage&quot; of being controlled by human beings. I have to ask you -- what good does that advantage do player casters when 1 or 2 nukes from a blue-con NPC can wipe out a PC caster's entire health bar in less time than a heal can be cast on them?<br><br>We're not just talking about a planned encounter where the caster is with a raiding party which has buffed and prepared for a big battle; we're talking about a caster who gets jumped by an NPC caster that spawns on top of them while they're simply trying to get from point A to point B in a regular hunting zone.<br><br>You want case-by-case? Okay in Maiden's Eye, take a goranga spiritseer for example. This is a non-named, regular-exp, regular-spawn NPC in Maiden ... which happens to nuke for 800-900 damage, and chain nukes. Now tell me, if a 60th level shadowknight with over 1400 armor class and 140+ MR gets nuked by that mob for over 800 damage per hit, how long is a 55th level pure caster going to last against that mob?<br><br>Bad AI is always going to be a poor excuse, considering AI is the basis for NPC encounters in this type of game. The designers could easily choose a better set of spells for NPC casters to have at their disposal commensurate to level, and the designers could easily add a more sensible specific order in which spells would be cast during an encounter, and could easily add more sensible NPC caster responses to situational variables. <br><br>Instead, they take the easy way out, and artificially enhance the casting ability of NPC mobs beyond the proportion of their actual levels.<br><br>Maybe those same designers should be placed in charge of player caster balancing.<br><br>/shrug<br><br>~Firemynd <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufiremynd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Firemynd</A> at: 6/7/02 8:28:44 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufiremynd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Firemynd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/7/02 11:33:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27552.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Paladins and wizards &gt; Druids</span><hr size=1> /ooc <br>By the way, if you're using Internet Explorer, you can right-click that screen shot and Zoom Out, to bring the page to a more comfortable reading width. I've regularly